BoutrosLab.utilities 1.9.8 2016-03-26 (Ren Sun)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NEW FEATURE
* Added calculate.mcc() which returns Matthew's Correlation Coefficient (MCC) for assessing model
	performance in binary classification when classes are imbalanced. Inputs are a vector of
	predicted classes and a vector of true classes

BoutrosLab.utilities 1.9.7 2016-03-11 (Christopher Lalansingh)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NEW FEATURE
* Added confusion.matrix() which generates a standard confusion matrix for a binary classifier in
	the form of a dataframe with addition attributes for common metrics (e.g. sensitivity,
	specificity, FDR, F1 score, accuracy, etc)
